hat are the limits of words in explanation and defense? Why was Jesus silent during his trial? Why did Socrates' most powerful apologia fail? What words, if any, work in prayer? Do words work against the fear of death? Out of this philosophical and religious questioning, Reflections on Jesus and Socrates throws new light on the compelling figures of these two and on the continuing meanings of their stories for us today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aPHILOSOPHY / Movements / Humanism.2bisacsh0 cprintz978030006695140uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030014633240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300146332423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300146332/original  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles